#### Issue details

There seems to be a bit of a buggy behaviour when working with colors in a pixmap. If you do setPixel with a color that doesn't have full alpha, it changes all the other color values. If you do getPixel you will get a different color than what you originally wanted.
This is really bugging me right now, because I wanted to save the colors (that I get by getPixel) in json and then load the json and get the same color. However, what happens is that the colors get darker and darker the more i load and save.
#### Reproduction steps/code

```
import com.badlogic.gdx.ApplicationAdapter;
import com.badlogic.gdx.Gdx;
import com.badlogic.gdx.backends.lwjgl.LwjglApplication;
import com.badlogic.gdx.graphics.Pixmap;
import com.badlogic.gdx.graphics.Pixmap.Format;

public class PixmapColor extends ApplicationAdapter {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        new LwjglApplication(new PixmapColor());
    }

    @Override
    public void create() {
        Pixmap pixmap = new Pixmap(64, 64, Format.RGBA8888);
        int color = 0xff0000dd; // red that is a bit transparent

        // Prints ff0000dd
        Gdx.app.log("PixmapColor", Integer.toHexString(color));

        pixmap.drawPixel(0, 0, color);

        // Prints wrong color: dd0000dd
        Gdx.app.log("PixmapColor", Integer.toHexString(pixmap.getPixel(0, 0)));

        pixmap.dispose();
    }

}
```
