Less an issue but suggestion:

When using the provided methods for checking intersection or contain of the [BoundingBox](https://libgdx.badlogicgames.com/nightlies/docs/api/com/badlogic/gdx/math/collision/BoundingBox.html) it always checks for validity first. 

`public boolean isValid () {
        return min.x < max.x && min.y < max.y && min.z < max.z;
    }`

this of course returns never true in a strict 2d environment and one has to set max.z > 0 manually. 

a solution could be

`public boolean isValid () {
        return min.x < max.x && min.y < max.y && min.z <= max.z;
    }`

but I dont know about the implications in 3d.

