#### Issue details

When rendering bitmap fonts directly, the bitmapfontdata scale effects the size of the drawn text. If a label using the same bitmap is rendered. the scale no longer has any effect (since 1.9.4)

I use the scale feature heavily with distance field fonts.
#### Reproduction code

[full compilable project](http://streefgames.com/bitmapfonttest.rar)

```
public class BitmapFontTest extends ApplicationAdapter
{
    SpriteBatch batch;

    Label bigLabel;
    Label smallLabel;
    BitmapFont big;
    BitmapFont small;


    @Override
    public void create()
    {
        batch = new SpriteBatch();
        small = new BitmapFont();
        big = new BitmapFont();

        small.getData().setScale(1.0f);
        big.getData().setScale(4.0f);

        bigLabel = new Label("not big label",new Label.LabelStyle(big, Color.WHITE));
        bigLabel.setPosition(0,100);
        smallLabel = new Label("small label",new Label.LabelStyle(big, Color.WHITE));
    }

    @Override
    public void render()
    {
        Gdx.gl.glClearColor(1, 0, 0, 1);
        Gdx.gl.glClear(GL20.GL_COLOR_BUFFER_BIT);
        batch.begin();
        bigLabel.draw(batch, 1.0f);
        smallLabel.draw(batch, 1.0f);
        big.draw(batch,"big font",100,125);
        small.draw(batch,"small font",100,25);
        batch.end();
    }

    @Override
    public void dispose()
    {
        batch.dispose();
        big.dispose();
        small.dispose();
    }
}
```
